==English==
===Etymology===
The surname of ''[[w:Don Quixote|Don Quixote]]'', the [[eponymous]] character in the novel by [[w:Miguel Cervantes|Miguel Cervantes]],<!-- or is it borrowed from a Spanish adjective derived from the name of the character? --> + '''[[-ic]]'''

===Pronunciation===
*(''[[RP]]''): /kwɪkˈsɒtɪk/, /<tt>kwIk"sQtIk</tt>/
*(''US''): kwĭksätʹĭk, /kwɪkˈsɑtɪk/, /<tt>kwIk"sAtIk</tt>/

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-more}}

#Possessing or acting with the desire to do [[noble]] and [[romantic]] deeds, without thought of realism and practicality.
#[[Impulsive]].
#Like [[w:Don Quixote|Don Quixote]]; romantic to extravagance; absurdly [[chivalric]]; apt to be deluded.

